GENERAL ASSEMBLY OF NORTH CAROLINA
SESSION 2025
H 1
HOUSE BILL 859
Short Title: Local Govts/Guaranteed Income Programs. (Public)
Sponsors: Representative Huneycutt.
For a complete list of sponsors, refer to the North Carolina General Assembly web site.
Referred to: Commerce and Economic Development, if favorable, State and Local
Government, if favorable, Rules, Calendar, and Operations of the House
April 10, 2025
1 A BILL TO BE ENTITLED
2 AN ACT PROHIBITING COUNTIES AND CITIES FROM ADOPTING OR ENFORCING
3 GUARANTEED INCOME PROGRAMS.
4 The General Assembly of North Carolina enacts:
5 SECTION 1. Article 6 of Chapter 153A of the General Statutes is amended by
6 adding a new section to read:
7 "§ 153A-145.13. Guaranteed income programs prohibited.
8 Unless expressly authorized by general or local law, a county shall not adopt or enforce any
9 ordinance, resolution, or policy that has the purpose or effect of making a payment to an
10 individual under a guaranteed income program. For purposes of this section, the term "guaranteed
11 income program" means a program under which an individual is issued an unconditional cash
12 payment on a regular basis to be used for any purpose by the individual. The term does not
13 include a program under which an individual is required to seek reemployment, perform work,
14 or attend training as a condition of a cash payment."
15 SECTION 2. Article 8 of Chapter 160A of the General Statutes is amended by
16 adding a new section to read:
17 "§ 160A-205.8. Guaranteed income programs prohibited.
18 Unless expressly authorized by general or local law, a city shall not adopt or enforce any
19 ordinance, resolution, or policy that has the purpose or effect of making a payment to an
20 individual under a guaranteed income program. For purposes of this section, the term "guaranteed
21 income program" means a program under which an individual is issued an unconditional cash
22 payment on a regular basis to be used for any purpose by the individual. The term does not
23 include a program under which an individual is required to seek reemployment, perform work,
24 or attend training as a condition of a cash payment."
25 SECTION 3. This act is effective when it becomes law.
*H859-v-1*

